      "source_title": "Envelope Protocol v1.0 (EP‑1)",
      "source_link": "https://app.notion.com/p/bd220dd4c12d44cfb2d3b97c2e35148a?pvs=1",
      "category": "protocol",
      "verbatim_excerpt": "Envelope Protocol v1.0 (EP‑1)\nPurpose:\nDefines the mandatory structure for all agent‑to‑agent communication. Ensures deterministic routing, auditability, replay protection, safety boundaries, consistent expectations, and no ambiguous messages.\nRequired Envelope Fields:\nBundle‑ID: Unique workflow identifier. Format: <SYSTEM>-<YYYYMMDD>-<HHMM>-<SEQ>\nTimestamp: UTC timestamp.\nFrom: Originating agent.\nTo: Target agent.\nPurpose: Human‑readable intent.\nPayload: Structured data.\nExpected Output: What the sender expects.\nFailure Mode: How to respond if action fails.\nRollback Instructions: How to reverse the action.\nExample:\nBundle-ID: AGENTOS-20260522-0434-01\nTimestamp: 2026-05-22T04:34:00Z\nFrom: orchestrator\nTo: worker\nPurpose: execute_task\nPayload:\ntask_type: resource_snapshot\nExpectedOutput:\nsnapshot: {}\nFailureMode:\nreturn_error: true\nRollback:\nnone\nRules of Use:\nAll messages must include a complete envelope.\nBundle‑ID cannot be modified.\nResponses must include the same Bundle‑ID.\nAll envelopes must be logged.\nNo agent may bypass the protocol.\nVersioning:\nEP‑1 is the initial stable version.\nSet page status to: Active — required for all agent communication.\n---\n[NOTION-AI-REPLY]"
    },
